&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;THE POSITION&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;Our roster has an opening with your name on it&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The&amp;nbsp;Sr.&amp;nbsp;Manager&amp;nbsp;of AI Operations &amp;amp; Strategy will play a critical role in helping scale and operationalize AI across the enterprise. This role sits at the intersection of AI, product, engineering, operations, and business transformation.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a highly cross-functional leadership and execution role designed for a strategic operator with strong consulting, program leadership, and organizational management experience. We are looking for someone who excels at bringing structure to ambiguity, driving alignment across senior stakeholders, coordinating complex initiatives, and ensuring teams execute effectively against strategic priorities.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You do not need to be a hands-on AI engineer or researcher. Instead, success in this role comes from the ability to understand how AI initiatives create business value, translate strategic goals into executable programs, and help teams deliver outcomes at scale.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role will exercise influence across AI Software Engineering, AI Product Management, and AI Platform Engineering while partnering closely with Security, Platform Engineering &amp;amp; Operations, Product Engineering, Data, Finance, and other business stakeholders.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role is ideal for someone with experience in technology strategy, transformation, operations, consulting, PMO leadership, and/or enterprise program management who thrives in fast-moving environments and enjoys solving complex organizational challenges.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In addition to the responsibilities outlined below, employees may be required to perform other duties as assigned to support evolving business priorities.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;THE GAME PLAN&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;Everyone on our team has a part to play&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;AI Operations &amp;amp; Strategic Execution&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner closely with the AI Engineering team to operationalize and execute strategic AI priorities across the organization.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Help coordinate organizational priorities, operating rhythms, planning processes, and cross-functional execution.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive alignment and coordination across partner organizations including other Corporate Technology teams (like Security, Platform Engineering &amp;amp; Operations, Product Engineering, Data, Infrastructure) as well as business stakeholders.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Establish and manage scalable operational mechanisms for roadmap planning, prioritization, executive reporting, portfolio management, governance reviews, and delivery tracking.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Help ensure AI initiatives remain aligned to business priorities, resource constraints, operational dependencies, and organizational goals.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinate complex, cross-functional AI programs spanning multiple teams, stakeholders, and delivery timelines.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prepare executive-level communications, updates, presentations, and operational reviews related to AI initiatives, investments, risks, and business impact.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify organizational bottlenecks, execution gaps, and operational inefficiencies and help drive resolution plans across teams.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;AI Product Strategy, Planning &amp;amp; Delivery&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Influence and help coordinate AI product roadmaps, prioritization processes, execution plans, measurement strategies, and operational rollout plans.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
